Here is the translation and analysis of the passage from Xunzi.

### (1) Translation

Marquis Wu of Wei deliberated on affairs of state and made the right decisions; none of his ministers could match his ability. After retiring from the court, he wore a look of joy.

Wu Qi stepped forward and asked, "Has Your Lordship ever heard the story of King Zhuang of Chu?"

Marquis Wu asked, "What about King Zhuang of Chu?"

Wu Qi replied, "King Zhuang of Chu deliberated on affairs and made the right decisions; none of his ministers could match him. Yet, after retiring from the court, he wore a look of worry. Shen Gong Wu Chen stepped forward and asked: 'Your Majesty retired with a look of worry; why is that?'

"King Zhuang replied: 'I deliberated on affairs and made the right decisions, yet none of my ministers could match me. That is why I am worried. There is a saying by Zhong Gui: "A ruler who finds himself a teacher shall become a true King; one who finds himself a friend shall become a Hegemon; one who finds those who can question him shall survive; but one who deliberates on his own with no one equal to him shall perish." Now, given my own unworthiness, yet none of my ministers can match me, my state is on the brink of perishing! That is why I am worried.'

"King Zhuang was worried about this, yet you, My Lord, are joyful over it."

Marquis Wu stepped back in humility, bowed twice, and said, "Heaven has sent the Master to correct my faults."

